value:
Four movements from the Suite for harpsichord in G minor, HWV 452, and (on the same fold as the Gigue) the Italian cantata "Quel fior che l'alba ride" (HWV 154).
Title from captions and first line.
The harpsichord movements are written on the recto only of three separate leaves and the first leaf of a fold; the leaves were originally numbered "1"-"4" (now mostly lost).
Holograph manuscript in ink.
Watermark p. 31-32, 37-40: "LVG" below fleur de lis over Strasbourg bend; countermark: "IV" (Burrows C30)
Watermark p. 33-36: Fleur de lis over Strasbourg bend ; countermark "IV" (Burrows B140)
Contents:
p. 31. Allemanda -- p. 33. Courante -- p. 35. Sarabande -- p. 37. Gigue -- p. 38-39. Quel fior che l'alba ride.
